The '''2005 Liège–Bastogne–Liège''' was the 91st edition of the [[Liège–Bastogne–Liège]], one of the [[Classic cycle races#The 'Monuments'|five monuments of cycling]]. [[Alexander Vinokourov]] was able to beat [[Jens Voigt]] after they had broken away from the pack 72&nbsp;km from the end. [[Michael Boogerd]] took the last spot on the podium after countering an attack from [[Cadel Evans]] on the final climb of the day.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://autobus.cyclingnews.com/road/2005/apr05/lbl05/?id=results | title=Vino the Vainqueur | author=Hedwig Kröner | work=Cycling News | date=24 April 2005 | accessdate=23 August 2011}}</ref>

