The '''Akademos Rally''' is an annual [[car rally]] held in [[Victoria, Australia]], by the [[Melbourne University Car Club]]. The event had its origins in 1961. The name was coined by the then-head of Motorsport in Australia as an amalgam of academic (Akadem) and motorsport (mos).

The event is a round of the [[Victorian Rally Championship]]. The Akademos Rally is a [[Confederation of Australian Motor Sport|CAMS]]-permitted event. As of the 2005 event, held in [[Alexandra, Victoria|Alexandra]], the event allows competitors to use [[pacenotes]]. Prior to 2005, the event was run as a "blind" event, where competitors are not allowed to view the course in the preceding six weeks.

