{{Infobox stadium | name = Estadio La Portada | image = La Portada La Serena.jpg | image_size = 250px | caption = the new stadium | location = [[La Serena, Chile]] | coordinates = {{Coord|29|54|40|S|71|15|07|W|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | opened = {{Start date|1952|08|26}} | reopened = {{Start date|2015|03|13}} | owner = Municipality of [[La Serena, Chile|La Serena]] | surface = grass | capacity = 18,243<ref name="conmebol">{{cite web|url=http://www.conmebol.com/es/copa-america-2015|title=Copa América 2015|work=conmebol.com}}</ref> | tenants = [[Deportes La Serena]] }} '''Estadio La Portada''' ({{IPA-es|la poɾˈtaða}}) is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[La Serena, Chile]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home stadium of [[Deportes La Serena]]. The stadium holds 18,243 people, was built in 1952, and completely renovated in 2015, in time for the [[2015 Copa America]].
