{{infobox country at games | NOC = CIV | NOCname = Comité National Olympique de Côte d'Ivoire | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1976 | flagcaption = [[Flag of Ivory Coast]] | oldcode = | website = | location = [[Montreal]] | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Ivory Coast]]''' competed at the '''[[1976 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], Canada. Ivory Coast and [[Senegal at the 1976 Summer Olympics|Senegal]] were the only two African nations that attended these Games.
==Results by event==
===[[Athletics at the 1976 Summer Olympics|Athletics]]=== '''Men's 4 × 100 m Relay''' *[[Kraarsene Konan]], [[Georges Kablan Degnan]], [[Gastom Kouadio]], and [[Amadou Meïté]] :* Heat &mdash; 40.23s :* Semi Finals &mdash; 40.64s (→ did not advance)
'''Men's Long Jump''' *[[Kouakou Brou]] :* Qualification &mdash; 7.20m (→ did not advance)
