The '''Kontinental Hockey League Players' Trade Union''' is the [[trade union]] of the professional [[ice hockey]] players who are under contract to any team in the [[Kontinental Hockey League]]. Headquartered in [[Moscow]], [[Russia]], it was founded in 2009 when the [[Russian Superleague]] gave way to the KHL.

