{{Infobox baseball biography |name=Lee Young-ha |position=[[Pitcher]] |team=Doosan Bears |number=50 |bats=Right |throws=Right |birth_date={{birth date and age|1997|11|01|df=y}} |debutleague=[[Korea Professional Baseball|KBO]] |debutyear=2017 |debutteam=[[Doosan Bears]] |statyear=2017 season |statleague=KBO |stat1label=[[Win–loss record (pitching)|Win–loss record]] |stat1value=3–3 |stat2label=[[Earned run average]] |stat2value=5.55 |stat3label=[[Strikeout]]s |stat3value=26 |teams=*[[Doosan Bears]] ([[2017 in baseball|2017]]&ndash;present)|birth_place=[[Seoul]]}}
'''Lee Young-ha''' ({{Korean|hangul=이영하}}; born 1 November 1997) is a South Korean professional baseball pitcher who is currently playing for the [[Doosan Bears]] of the [[Korea Baseball Organization]]. He graduated from [[Sunrin Internet High School]] and was selected for the Doosan Bears by the first draft in 2016. He joined the Doosan Bears in 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.koreabaseball.com/Record/Player/PitcherDetail/Total.aspx?playerId=66291|title=KBO 홈페이지 Player info|last=스포츠투아이|first=|date=|website=KBO|language=ko|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=10 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3047887|title=Explosive at bat and a safe pair of hands|website=Korea JoongAng Daily|access-date=2018-05-10}}</ref>
