{{Infobox_Stadium | stadium_name = Zaqatala "Simurq" stadium | image = Zaqatala City Stadium.jpg | image_size = 250px | nickname = | fullname = Zaqatala "Simurq" Stadium | location = [[Zaqatala (city)|Zaqatala]], [[Azerbaijan]] | built = 2008 | owner = [[FK Simurq Zaqatala]] | operator = {{flagicon|BUL}} Dynamic Sport | surface = Artificial field | construction_cost = US$12 million | architect = "Khazar" center of scientific and technical creativity of youth | former_names = | tenant = <center>[[FK Simurq Zaqatala]]</center> | seating_capacity = 3,500 | dimensions = 105x68 }} '''Zaqatala "Simurq"''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Zaqatala (city)|Zaqatala]], [[Azerbaijan]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and it considered as home ground of [[FK Simurq Zaqatala]], since October 2008.
The stadium was built in the area Galadyuzyu in place of old arena. The total area of 2.3 hectares. The draft was prepared by the Bulgarian "Dynamic Resource", commissioned by the company "General Constructions". The work took place from 2006 to August 2008. At its construction has been spent around US$12 million. The stadium holds 3500 spectators, one-sided platform for VIP-guests, calculated at 181. The main field, the size of which 105x68 meters of artificial surface, several small training lawns, artificial lighting, drainage and modern electronic street system, running track, tickets for ticketing, special places for the disabled, a large heating system, water reservoir at 300 cubic meters - this is the basic indicators of the stadium «Simurq».<ref>[http://94.20.30.18/Stadion.html Zaqatala Olimpiya İdman Kompleksinin Stadionu]{{dead link|date=July 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} {{az icon}}</ref>
The first floor of building is only for teams and judges. There are rooms for each team, doctors and massage rooms, a laboratory for doping tests, the press center. On the second floor there are Internet cafes, bars, VIP-bar, but on the third floor there seats for the press.
